r promotion, branding and distribution, consumers are using these devices as a means of navigating public and private space. These devices are not just changing the way we spend and value our time, but also how we interact with others and transform our sense of the politics of space.By examining the four main locations of the procrastination economy-the workplace, the commute, the waiting room, and the "connected" living room-Ethan Tussey illuminates the relationship between the entertainment industry and the digitally empowered public.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 08. Jun 2020) 0aProcrastination. 0aRecreationxEconomic aspects. 0aWork environment. 4acommunity. 4aconsumer behavior. 4acultural politics. 4aengagement. 4aentertainment industry. 4amobile devices. 4anew media. 4aphone apps. 4ascreen time. 4asmartphones. 4asocial connections. 4asocial media. 4auser experience. 4awasting time. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Media Studies.2bisacsh40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781479858934423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781479858934.jpg  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK